  dialogueLines:
  - "Alright. Welcome to the Director\u2019s Booth. This is your command center before
    you send anyone into the arena. Here, you\u2019ll handle everything: who goes
    in, what they carry, how you plan to keep the audience hooked. Let\u2019s go
    through the options."
  - "First up \u2014 Director's Board. This is where you spend your Sigils to unlock
    permanent upgrades. Think of it as your personal improvement plan."
  - "Cast lets you choose which prisoner you\u2019ll send into the arena next. Each
    one has different strengths and styles."
  - Loadout is where you customize your loadout. Equip boosters and plan your strategy
    before you head in.
  - "Check out the Intel for all the intel you\u2019ve unlocked. Learn about other
    characters, weapons, and props."
  - Visit the Gear Room to purchase new plays for your Playbook. More plays mean
    more ways to surprise the crowd and keep ratings high.
  - Settings is pretty straightforward. Adjust your controls, audio, visuals. Make
    it all feel right.
  - "You\u2019ll also get Broadcast Alerts when something important happens. Stay
    sharp\u2014the audience loves surprises."
  - "Now about Sigils. You\u2019ll earn these during your runs. Spend them to unlock
    progression upgrades and boost your chances."
  - Card Points are special currency for unlocking new cards. More cards means more
    ways to keep the audience guessing.
  - Cash is used to unlock more prisoners to send into the arena. More contestants
    mean more variety for your show.
  - "Metrics gives you a full breakdown of your performance. Wins, strategies, favorite
    gear\u2014it\u2019s all tracked here"
  - Segments shows you your current goals and objectives. Keep an eye on it for extra
    rewards.
  - Showcase is for when you want to shake things up. Special rules, tougher conditions,
    better bragging rights.
  - "And finally\u2026 Action. When you\u2019re ready to put on the show, this is
    where it begins. Choose your contestant and send them in."
